commit_list.message:
fmt now prints newlines correctly, and also fa returns correct free
names

added an equivariant version of a the matching function. Fixed a bug
where rewriting would return the old term instead of rewritten in the
case of tuples in rewrite function.
better debuggin printing for the unification function

normalization
also bugfix in elimination rule

added constants for reusing unification as a matching algorihtm.
Constants should not be exposed to a user.

require.ML is now standalone. There only dependencies are that from
standard library.

corrected the subsitution composition order in the unification
implementation and shift permutation application in the substitution
function.

small fix: rule F correctly constructs the variable now

also added some test cases and debugging print for unification

yet another design for the support of shift permutations in the
unification implementation.

This time around a shift permutation is associated with the variable
term, the same as with variable swapping. However, shift permutations
preceed name swapping permutations and are not applicable to ordinary
terms.

Added 'unify' keyword to the specification language. Also added missing
cases for running unification algorithm.
changed the references to the new dir
copied reusbale library parts from pwb/ directory
pnl file for the lambda calculus
refactored the unification implementation. More work needs to be done.
the beginnings of a unification algorithm
completed the implementation of the free atoms function fa
added the skeleton for the astToSpec function
removed the old parsing code for the sorts
properly parsing both sorts and terms
all of the term parse, however, still need to fix the tuples

more file is parse (I should thougt have a separate AST from the actual
representation)
initial implementation of nominal terms and logics
